From the retrieved text chunks, particularly Chunk 39, I can see the definition of the relaxed accuracy metric in Equation 4:

\[
\text{Acc}_{\text{relaxed}} = \frac{1}{n} \sum_{i=1}^n \left( \mathbbm{1}\{x_i = y_i\} + \lambda \cdot \mathbbm{1}\{x_i \approx y_i\} \right)
\]

This equation shows that the relaxed accuracy metric combines exact matches (using the indicator function \(\mathbbm{1}\{x_i = y_i\}\)) with partial matches (using \(\mathbbm{1}\{x_i \approx y_i\}\)), where partial matches are scaled by a hyperparameter \(\lambda\). This directly corresponds to option C.

Therefore, the correct answer is:

<answer>C. It incorporates a weighted sum of exact matches and partial matches, where partial matches are scaled by a hyperparameter λ.</answer>
