On Page 3, the paper explains that under the neural-collapse regime, the last-layer weight vectors align with class prototypes, and the update’s energy is distributed across class directions. The entropy is then approximated as the Shannon entropy of the normalized class-space spread, which increases when the update’s energy is spread more evenly and decreases when it concentrates in a few directions. This suggests that the logarithm is used to interpret the entropy as information content, reflecting how uniformly the client’s update contributes across different class directions.

